. Discussion questions are included to help students with research assignments and papers. Both professors and students will find its narrative, chronological approach a useful guide to the history of this important area of the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  aclass.  acultural anthropology.  aethnography.  agender.  ahistorical context.  ahistorical reference.  alatinx studies.  amexican american immigrants.  apolitical activists.  arace.  ascholars.  asocial activists.  asocioeconomic position.  asociology.1 aConniff, Michael L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGauss, Susan M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052028902440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096382540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520963825423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520963825/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles